**ATTENTION NYC**

Here’s a sweaty, adorable photo of me to tell you all THIS:

This Sunday, January 29, my friends @schirmer.theatrical and I are premiering a brand new live concert series at the fabulous @bellhouseny called “The Brooklyn Variety Ramble” 🔥

“The Brooklyn Variety Ramble” is a celebration of all of the incredible country, americana, folk and roots music and the artists who write, record and perform it in the greatest f*cking city in the world.

Hosted by the insanely hilarious Ali Clayton of the @yallgaypod (recently voted one of @vulture best comedy pods of 2022) and featuring the outrageously talented @rebeccahavilandandwhiskeyheart, @oneptwoz & @juliewilliamsmusic as our inaugural guest artists, the @brooklyn.variety.ramble is not an evening to miss.
Ever. Got it. Good 😘

I’m so stoked to have been a part of an amazing team creating the show and to front the most badass cohort of players anywhere around, the fabulous BVR House Band: 

@cameronrmitchell - pedal steel
@_johnchong - drums
@briankilleenbass - bass
@albis_music - guitar
yours truly - trying to keep up

Will there be a special duet between myself and the incomparable Brittain Ashford (aka the greatest insta handle ever @kittendonut)?
F*ck around, come on down and find out 💛

Sunday 1/29
@bellhouseny - 7:30 PM

to be able make something beautiful out of pain has been the greatest gift life has ever given me.
here’s a little piece of that.

“Nola” is streaming everywhere now.

Dig it.

The ultimate thank you to my best friend and musical compadre @bryanjdawley for producing this incredible track, for pushing me out of my comfort zone and making me dig deeper. and for the strolls.

to @eleonoredenig for truly, spectacularly making every beautiful, stringed maniacal sound in my head a reality and so much more. fucking queen of queens. thank you.

to @valleyofjames for lending her magically haunting voice so perfectly  to the ghost of our titular character. another queen. thank you, CJ.

okay, thanks for listening. share with your friends and lovers, moms and dads, dogs and cats, etc.

it’s sad boy fall. get with it.

I used to walk the streets of Hollywood, from my apartment on Cherokee Ave down to the liquor store for a package of Kents (because that’s what Tom Waits smoked…psst, go listen to “Pony” too) and then all around the surrounding blocks until the sun rose over the big sign.
I was looking for something.
Still don’t know what.

I was scared and alone and disconnect and…lost?
That’s too much. 
Didn’t feel like it was too much back then though, I guess.

I never figured much out those long, solitary peripatetic nights.
But did get this lovely melody from the ghost of the sunset grill, the wannabes still haunting the rainbow and the losers like me on the street who’d pass with a knowing glance, a slight nod and, in my own head at least, a silent half-hug saying “we’re in this together, pal.”

as @john_prine once said: “we are the lonely”

fair enough. 

thanks for listening. go tell it on the mountain.
“Nola” is streaming everywhere.

The following story is absolutely true, as best as I can remember it, and almost too sweet to understand.

A few nights ago I was visited in my dreams by my father. 

I was walking down the street in my neighborhood when I happened upon a younger, healthy him, standing on the corner looking down at his phone. 
He seemed to be about my age, meeting me in the middle after all this time, already salt and peppered like me but with so many miles to go yet. 

‘Hi, dad,’ I said.
‘Hi, son.’

He smiled at me as I glanced down at his phone to realize that he had been looking at these photos of my wedding day. 

‘I really love these pictures, son.’
‘I do too, dad.’

He hugged me tightly then and said, ‘I gotta go. The gummy is hitting me.’

Then I woke up. 

I realized later when I was telling K about my dream that my father only comes to me when I feel especially happy and content and…safe.

Anyway, this first photo is my favorite one ever taken of Kendall, standing there looking like a masterpiece with the sun shining on her in on our cozy little apartment in Brooklyn, my favorite place.

Everything is everything.

And to the greatest, @mollypeachphoto, thank you for capturing this day, this time, these moments. These are perfect.

Dad agrees.
